---
import DocsLayout from '../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import { ROUTES } from '../lib/routes';

const seoTitle = "API Documentation & Integration Guide";
const seoDescription = "Technical integration guide for Sentinel deterministic AI compliance. cURL, Node.js, and CLI implementation details.";
---

<DocsLayout title={seoTitle} description={seoDescription}>
  <Fragment slot="sidebar">
    <div class="sidebar-section">Introduction</div>
    <a href="#quickstart">Quickstart</a>
    <a href="#architecture">Architecture</a>
    
    <div class="sidebar-section">API Reference</div>
    <a href="#curl">cURL</a>
    <a href="#nodejs">Node.js</a>
    <a href="#python">Python</a>
    
    <div class="sidebar-section">CI/CD & Infrastructure</div>
    <a href="#cli">CI/CD Integration</a>
    
    <div class="sidebar-section">Resources</div>
    <a href={ROUTES.aiComplianceTools}>Compliance Tools</a>
    <a href={ROUTES.aiComplianceFaq}>Technical FAQ</a>
    <a href={ROUTES.governanceComparison}>Tool Comparison</a>
  </Fragment>

  <h1 id="quickstart">Sentinel API</h1>
  <p>The definitive engineering standard for deterministic AI compliance. Integrate technical evidence collection directly into your development lifecycle.</p>

  <div class="alert">
    <strong>EU AI Act Regulation (EU) 2024/1689</strong> &mdash; 
    Sentinel helps teams fulfill technical documentation requirements under Annex IV.
  </div>

  <h2 id="architecture">Architecture</h2>
  <p>Sentinel operates as a <strong>Zero-Egress</strong> infrastructure layer. Compliance logic is executed locally within your CI/CD runner or development environment. Your source code, model weights, and proprietary training data never leave your secure perimeter.</p>

  <h3>Sovereign Evidence Collection</h3>
  <p>By using deterministic article mapping, Sentinel translates repository signals (metadata, configs, oversight logs) into verifiable compliance artifacts.</p>

  <h2 id="curl">cURL Implementation</h2>
  <div class="lang-label">shell</div>
  <pre><code>curl -X POST https://api.gettingsentinel.com/v1/scan \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_KEY" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d @manifest.json</code></pre>

  <h2 id="nodejs">Node.js SDK</h2>
  <div class="lang-label">javascript</div>
  <pre><code><span class="hl-purple">import</span> &#123; Sentinel &#125; <span class="hl-purple">from</span> <span class="hl-str">'@sentinel/sdk'</span>;

<span class="hl-comment">// Initialize deterministic engine</span>
<span class="hl-purple">const</span> client = <span class="hl-purple">new</span> Sentinel(&#123; apiKey: process.env.SENTINEL_KEY &#125;);

<span class="hl-comment">// Execute local compliance check</span>
<span class="hl-purple">const</span> result = <span class="hl-purple">await</span> client.scan(<span class="hl-str">'./manifest.json'</span>);
console.log(result.compliance_status); <span class="hl-comment">// "COMPLIANT"</span></code></pre>

  <h2 id="python">Python client</h2>
  <div class="lang-label">python</div>
  <pre><code><span class="hl-purple">from</span> sentinel <span class="hl-purple">import</span> SentinelEngine

engine = SentinelEngine(api_key=<span class="hl-str">"sk_live_..."</span>)
report = engine.verify_manifest(<span class="hl-str">"manifest.json"</span>)

<span class="hl-purple">if</span> report.is_compliant:
    print(<span class="hl-str">"Compliance check passed"</span>)</code></pre>

  <h2 id="cli">CI/CD Integration</h2>
  <p>Run Sentinel in your GitHub Actions or GitLab pipelines to block non-compliant PRs before they hit production.</p>

  <div class="lang-label">yaml</div>
  <pre><code><span class="hl-comment"># CI/CD integration (exit 0 = COMPLIANT, exit 1 = NON_COMPLIANT)</span>
sentinel-scan ./manifest.json &amp;&amp; kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml</code></pre>

  <h2 id="ai-compliance-tools">AI Compliance Tools</h2>
  <p>Sentinel is a deterministic compliance infrastructure designed for engineering teams building High-Risk AI systems under the EU AI Act. By integrating directly into development workflows, Sentinel provides a technical evidence layer that links repo-level signals, manifests, and rule evaluations.</p>
  
  <p>The system supports <strong>zero-egress scanning</strong>, allowing rule verification to occur locally or within isolated enterprise infrastructure. To understand how deterministic scanners differ from traditional governance platforms, see the <a href={ROUTES.governanceComparison} style={{ color: 'var(--cyan)' }}>Sentinel vs AI Governance Tools</a> comparison. For specific technical queries, refer to our <a href={ROUTES.aiComplianceFaq} style={{ color: 'var(--cyan)' }}>Compliance FAQ</a> and <a href={ROUTES.aiComplianceTools} style={{ color: 'var(--cyan)' }}>technical explainer</a>.</p>

  <div class="alert" style={{ marginTop: '48px' }}>
    <strong>Ready to automate compliance?</strong> &mdash;
    <a href="/dashboard/login" style={{ color: 'var(--cyan)' }}>Get your Free Developer Key &rarr;</a>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
